netcat: Python based TCP client/server networking tool.

SYNOPSIS
python netcat.py [options]

DESCRIPTION

A lightweight Python Netcat implementation supporting TCP connections, remote command execution, file uploads, and interactive shells. 
Designed for learning networking and security concepts in lab environments.

OPTIONS
-c, --command        Start interactive command shell
-e, --execute CMD    Execute a command on connection
-l, --listen         Run in listen (server) mode
-p, --port PORT      Target port (default: 5555)
-t, --target IP      Target IP address
-u, --upload FILE    Upload file to server

EXAMPLES
python netcat.py -l -p 5555 -c
python netcat.py -t 192.168.1.108 -p 5555
python netcat.py -l -u test.txt
echo "Hi" | python netcat.py -t 192.168.1.108 -p 135

SECURITY NOTICE

⚠️ Use only on authorized systems.
For educational and defensive security purposes only.
